# What is the difference between Drafts and All projetcs
# Drafts
-> We can able to create Multitple pages in Drafts
-> We can able to create New Design file in Drafts
-> We can able to create New FigJam Board file in Drafts
-> We can able to create New Slide Deck file in Drafts

# All projects
-> We don't have chance to create multiple pages, we can able to only Threee pages.

-> Mostly we will work in Drafts, If you want to share to someone then you will move into teams.

-> Suppose if you want more pages in all projects like Drafts, First we create project in Drafts and add pages then you move into All projects

# We have four different types of Panels
-> File panel  --> Before we used to call it layers panels
-> Assets panel
-> Design panel
-> prototype panel

# File Panel
-> We can able to create multiple pages
-> Whatever we draw in canvas it will appear in layer panel

# Design Panel
-> We can see to change the canvas coluor and obacity before select any object
-> We can export our canvas

-> We can see the below properties of object after select any object
    -> We can see the name of the object in that place we have some options like
        -> Create Component
        -> Use as mask
        -> Union
        -> Edit in three ...

    -> Position
       -> We can change the position and rotate the angle
    -> Layout
       -> We can see the width and height of the object
       -> If select link it will increase both width and depth at a time while we increasin width or depth
    -> Appearance
       -> We can see the obacity
       -> We can change the shapes at corner places
    -> Fill     -> We can fill up colour in object
    -> Stroke   -> We can add the colours to boarders, we can add the boarders with gaps
    -> Efforts  -> We can get the Shadow efforts to the object
    -> Export


